act row-level checks.\n265: - Use planContract as upstream planning ownership evidence; resolve its alignmentFindings by updating plannedPhase/matrix/platform evidence or by documenting sourceOverride/analysisGap when source inspection disagrees.\n266: - Keep grouped business behavior discoverable through precise target endpoints; avoid closing unrelated features only through root/shell/whole-file endpoints.\n267: - Merge source files only when it improves target clarity and still preserves per-feature evidence, tests, and controllable file size.\n268: - Treat mustComplete entries as the current phase's executable row-level task list.\n269: - Use behaviorAudit as the current phase behavior audit; it checks closed critical/high rows for source behavior, target behavior, parity, and verification evidence.\n270: - Use uiContract entries as static-analysis planning aids, not complete UI specifications: preserve listed source-visible screen structure, route/back behavior, actions, state feedback, and visual evidence needs, then re-read source/resources/navigation for UI behavior the static analysis may have missed.\n271: - Do not close the phase while current-phase critical/high entries are open, weakly deferred, or missing evidence.\n272: - For every closed critical/high source feature, record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence in source-coverage-matrix.json.\n273: - A build pass alone is not per-feature verification; cite tests, manual/emulator evidence, or explicit verificationEvidence for behavior closure.\n274: - Use implemented-simplified only with concrete simplification reason, preserved-behavior explanation, target endpoints or tests, and source/platform evidence.\n275: - If a suitable HarmonyOS/Cangjie API, Kit, example, or package exists for a platform capability, use it or record a platform replacement; do not close the item with local mock data, sample data, in-memory simulation, or another fallback.\n276: - Use deferred only for concrete blockers; otherwise implement faithfully or platform-replace with evidence.\n277: - Update source-coverage-matrix.json/md and platform-capability-check.json/md before phase completion.\n278: - If this checklist is empty but the phase has real scope in plan.md/plan.json, assign plannedPhase values first.\n\n(End of file - total 278 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Phase Task Checklist\n\n- Phase: `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources`\n\n## Purpose\n\nCurrent-phase task checklist generated from the agent-maintained source coverage matrix and platform capability check. Use it before editing and update the matrix/check after work.\n\n## Summary\n\n| metric | value |\n| --- | --- |\n| phaseFeatureEntries | 49 |\n| phaseCriticalHighFeatureEntries | 44 |\n| mustCompleteFeatureEntries | 28 |\n| needsEvidenceFeatureEntries | 0 |\n| deferredOrFallbackFeatureEntries | 3 |\n| coveredFeatureEntries | 13 |\n| phaseSourceFiles | 19 |\n| phasePlatformCapabilityEntries | 1 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\phase-task-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782533581221,"end":1782533581230}},"id":"prt_f0747e9a0001oQK3FHgDko2J30","sessionID":"ses_0f8b84a87ffeugHsJw5ZQ49CGn","messageID":"msg_f0747d889001GggK5NbhCTyzD1"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782533581456,"sessionID":"ses_0f8b84a87ffeugHsJw5ZQ49CGn","part":{"id":"prt_f0747ea8d001fHxtRJSR8HzgFU","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"df5a0a8c2645641bc4f5f611062c856e3bc67eaa","messageID":"msg_f0747d889001GggK5NbhCTyzD1","sessionID":"ses_0f8b84a87ffeugHsJw5ZQ49CGn","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":17669,"input":17403,"output":266,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0}}
